HEADWORD: Sarcolemma
<hw>Sar`co*lem"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>sa`rx</grk>, <grk>sa`rkos</grk>, flesh + <?/ rind, skin.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The very thin transparent and apparently
homogeneous sheath which incloses a striated muscular fiber; the
myolemma.</def>⟦br⟧
